 <br/> <h3>STEP-2</h3>After uploading the package above, you will have to modify configuration file that can be found on the folder name <b>inc</b>. Just make some changes like server host, user name, password and database name. Upload or replace modified configuration file. Now import a file named statics.sql(can be found on inc folder) into your database. This will create the required table for statics.  <font color='red'><b>Note</b></font>:- Please make a backup of the tables, if you are using the existing table for the statics, this is for safety of data-loss in case of any changes. Configuration will be like this:<div class="code"> <b>modify Connection.php</b><hr/>$host = 'your_host'; /* localhost */ <br/>$user = 'username'; /* root */ <br/> $pass = 'password'; /* blank */ <br/> $data = 'database'; / databse name */ <br/> </div> <br/><b>How to get Statics</b>:- Add the following line at the starting of any page where you want to get the statics: <div class="code"> require_once('statics.php'); <br/> $statics = new statics(); <br/>
 $guest = $statics->Guest(); <br/> $membr = $statics->Members(); <br/> $statics = "Guest Online:$guest | Users Online:$membr";
 </div> Now you can show the statics at any place on that page by printing it or echo it i.e. print(statics); or echo $statics; thats all. If every thing is ok then you will get result like this:<br/><div class='code'><b>Statics Online</b><hr/>Guest Online: 23<br/>Users Online: 56<br/></div><b><u>ABOUT SECURITY:-</u></b><br/>Your database configuration is secured and normaly it can't be access by any person untill you will delete a security file <font color="#D40055">.HTACCESS</font>, we recommend you, never delete this file otherwise your database information may be leeked. And you know what will happen if your database information is shared. See our <a href="http://techsdl.info/about.php?cat=website&type=terms">terms & condition</a> of use of any software for more..<br/></div></body></html>
